- "higher-than-average salaries" means the average mean salary is greater than the overall average mean salary for the year 2022;
- "golden weave" is a metaphor for the groups that meet the criteria of having a higher average mean salary.

- "economic prosperity" refers to regions with high average salaries;
- "soaring above the national average" means the average salary in the region is greater than the overall average salary for all regions in 2022;
